s\nSlippers for Xmas\nAlways an Acceptable Gift\nNever have we offered better values. J 4 W\nX. There are slippers here to please y\nx. every man. g\nJ Make your selections while sizes and JMW\nstyles are complete.\nStage \u201cGiants\u201d Vanished,\nSkinner Declares\nNEW YORK. Dec. 15.\u2014There\nare no outstanding \u201cgiants\u2019* of\nthe American theater today like\nEdwin Booth, Otis Skinner, dean\nof American actors, declared at\na faculty-student tea held by the\nNew York University Y. M. C. A.,\nand attended by more than 150\nstudents and faculty members.\nMr. Skinner said:\n\u201cThe general acting of the\ntheater is good, but no one\nstands out simply because other\nactors are good. The theater of\ntoday is better than the thea\nter of yesterday as a result of\nthe scientific perfection of\nlighting effects and scenery im\nprovements.\n\u201cThe audience of today, is too\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMES\ncynical. In order to secure the\nmost out of the theater we\nmust be like children. We must\nbelieve that what we see on the\nstage actually happened.\n\u201cTalking pictures will never\nMU the stage. The present de\npression of the theater will not\npermanently affect it, although\nthere are many actors selling\napples now. Drama eventually\nwill dominate and be prominent\nonce again.\u201d\nYear telephone will plnee .von in Im\nmediate touch with the people itdver\ntloiaa their service* to you la the\nBISISERB SERVICE niRECTOBY of\ntoday** Classified Ado.\nVa. School League\nAsks Ban on Gifts\nBERRYVILLE, Va., Dec. 15.\nThe School League of Berryville\nat a recent meeting adopted a\nresolution requesting that public\nrefrain from giving presents dur\ning the Christmas season.\nProponents of the measure\nstated that in view of the finan\ncial conditions which have arisen\nas a result of the drought and\nbusiness depression, it would be\na good idea to dtsnense with un\nnecessary items of expense.\nM a tc h I e\nVAI IIFC\nWashington's\nGMesttfeuM)\nBecause You Can