 E. H. Hale, aided by Capt.\nThomas J.\u2018 Frailey. Other com\nmittee heads are Major Julius I.\nPeyser. Capt. John Lewis Smith,\nThomas E. Franklin, Dr. Mil\nburn F. Fowler, Russell Clarkson,\nForest F. Bartl, Bernard C. Mc-\nGee, Sam Berlin, Martin A. Dyer.\nMONDAY\u2014DECEMBER 15\u20141930\nGirls to Distribute\n3JSOb Toys to Poor\nGirl Reserves, will distribute\n3,500 toys on Christmas Eve to\nchildren in 11 or more institu\ntions connected with the Com\nmunity Chest.\nMrs. William McClellan Ritter,\nMrs. Harry Norment, Mrs. Stow\nell Smith, Miss Caroline Boak and\nMrs. Harry Blee have been direct\ning the girls in mending and re\npainting thousands of toys do\nnated by more fortunate boys and\ngirls.\nAlleged Abductors\nFace Finnish Trial\nHELSINGFORDS. Des. 15.\u2014The\ntrial of General Vallenius, former\nchief Finnish general staff;\nColonel Kuussari, Governor Jas\nkari and others accused of the\nabduction of former President\nStahlberg, began in the district\nprison, as the authorities did not\ncare to risk taking the accused\nfrom the prison.\nArmed guards were posted\naround the prison and in the\ncourtroom.\n3-A Auto* Offered\nFor Charity Work\nThe American Automobile Amo\nelation haa tendered the use of\nits service cars to the Salvation\nArmy for the distribution of\nChristmas baskets to needy fam\nilies* in the District of Columbia.\nErnest N. Smith, executive vice\npresident of the A A. A., has an\nnounced that 200 employes have\nvoted to go without their usual\nthree-A Christmas party this year\nand devote the money spent on\nthis celebration to furnishing\nChristmas baskets to the poor of\nWashington.\n9","height":"30201","width":"24252"}}
